#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Accused Parliament arsonist, Zandile Mafe, has again refused to leave the Pollsmoor Correctional Service Facility. Mafe was due to attend his pre-trial proceedings on Friday but was a no show. It has been more than a year since a fire ravaged Parliament in Cape Town. READ:Â Zandile Mafe's pre-trial hearing postponed Mafe was arrested in January last year and has made several court appearances. He was also sent to a psychiatric institution for a short period and was later released. The state says its ready, but Mafe's lawyers want to apply for him to be evaluated to see if he's fit to stand trial. Watch the video above for more details on this story.